reviews.review_text: The Perfect Place To Visit I've never listened to much of 1983. I've never liked the setlists or the decline in Jerry's health. But recently I've been delving in...and I can see how I wrong I was. This is a great show. This aud is dialed in..the sound is perfect. The show is great. Particularly the second set. Listen to it.

Yellow Light I was at this show...just drove from SLC where we saw the Dinosaurs the day before @ Salt Aire..venue out on the great salt lake that looked like a mini taj mahal...Robert Hunter and friends made up the band...heard "Liberty" for the first time...only 40 folks at the show...had us all arm in arm in a circle doing the hokey pokey...Roadies from the band tipped us off to this show that was add to the end of summer tour...gave us a few hits of yellow light to enjoy...combine that and the music and I was sent hi in the sky...mad dancing in the dust in a circle of redwoods..the music was vibrating throughout the roots beneath your feet...kept me from being fused with the sun :)

2nd Set God Made it Click Yeah. I was there. God made it click in the second set. 
Beautiful atmosphere surrounded by pine and fir trees, Anchor Steam on tap, colorful vendors, fluffy clouds, mushrooms and plenty of port-a-potties.
Nice show! This is a sweet-sounding audience pull of a solid and fun show!
